________________________________________________________________________

Memo

Neeraj Arora                   03.10.2011  07:28:38
Hi Yasuo,

As per our discussion, I have gone through SAP Note: 1317925 and it is
perfectly fine. Let me clarify the things below:

If you check in Desginer 8.1, the minimum target version is "Adobe
Reader 7.0.5 or later", which customer was using for his template. Now,
when he opens and save the same template in Designer 9.0.1.., then
template version of a template will not change automatically because the
minimum target version of Designer 9.0.1 is also "Adobe Reader 7.0.5 or
later". Now, in this case customer will not be able to use the new
feature of Designer 9 but there will not be any issue related to
behavior of a template as it was before. So, template will behave in a
same way as it was before. Now, if customer wants to use new feature of
Desginer 9.0.1 as well, then he can upgrade the template version
explicitly. In this case, new template version will take care of new
features of Designer 9.0 and the <original > tag in a template will take
care of behavior as it was showing in old template. So, there should not
be any problem for customer to upgrade to Desginer 9.0.

Regards,
Neeraj

